Parade of Worker-Peasant Red Guards Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- A parade of the Worker-Peasant Red Guards was held at Kim Il Sung Square with splendor on Sept. 9 to celebrate the 60th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were senior officials of the party, the army and the state, the chairpersons of the friendly parties, deputies to the Supreme People's Assembly, officials of the party, armed forces and power bodies, public organizations, ministries and national institutions, anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters, servicepersons of the Korean People's Army, officials in the fields of science, education, culture and arts, public health and media, heroes, persons of distinguished services and working people in Pyongyang, the chief of the Pyongyang Mission of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front, a congratulatory group of Koreans in Japan and other congratulatory groups and delegations of Koreans overseas and overseas compatriots, diplomatic envoys of various countries and staff members of foreign embassies, representatives of international organizations here, foreign delegations, delegations of organizations for the study of the Juche idea and friendship and solidarity organizations and other foreign guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Amid the playing of "Song of General Kim Il Sung" and "Song of General Kim Jong Il" a 21-gun salute boomed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Chun, vice-chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission, made a speech. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that holding the parade of the Worker-Peasant Red Guards on the auspicious occasion of the 60th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK is a striking manifestation of the unshakable faith and will of the army and people of the DPRK to demonstrate internally and externally the validity and vitality of the policy of putting all people under arms which has been successfully implemented at a new higher stage under the guidance of President Kim Il Sung and the Workers' Party of Korea and the invincible national power of Songun Korea and accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He declared that the DPRK would continue bolstering the self-defensive war deterrent unless the U.S. imperialists and their followers give up the policy for stifling the DPRK. If another war breaks out in this land, the DPRK will mercilessly punish the aggressors and accomplish the historic cause of national reunification, the greatest desire of the nation, without fail, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then the parade started. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Led by the column of Kim Il Sung University, the column of Kim Chaek University of Technology and the columns of the Worker-Peasant Red Guards in every province, the columns of the Young Red Guards and revolutionary schools marched past the tribune of honor in fine array, demonstrating the might of the army and people single-mindedly united around the headquarters of the revolution and the majestic appearance of the militia forces of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then columns of the Worker-Peasant Red Guards equipped with powerful combat equipment of Korean type including multiple rocket launchers and anti-aircraft guns moved past the square. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the paraders passed through streets amid the warm welcome of Pyongyangites along the tens of km-long route.

Torchlight Soiree Marks 60th Birthday of DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- A torchlight soiree of youth and students "The Homeland of Songun" was held at Kim Il Sung Square Tuesday to mark the 60th anniversary of the foundation of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were senior officials of the Party, the army and the state, the chairman of a friendly party, deputies to the Supreme People's Assembly, officials of the party, armed forces and power organs, social organizations, ministries and national institutions, anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters, servicepersons of the KPA, officials in the fields of science, education, culture and arts, public health and media, heroes, persons of distinguished services, working people in the city, the chief of the Pyongyang Mission of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front, the congratulatory group of Koreans in Japan and other congratulatory groups and delegations of overseas compatriots and Koreans overseas, diplomatic envoys of various countries and staff members of different embassies and representatives of international organizations here, foreign delegations, delegations of organizations for the study of the Juche idea and friendship and solidarity organizations and foreign guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The torchlight soiree started. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the band solemnly played "Leader Is Always With Us" and "My Great Country", the participants formed a huge flag of the Republic and the title of the soiree "The Homeland of Songun" on the square. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The youth and students changed the formations of torchlight columns to the tune of the loud chorus "The Song of General Kim Il Sung" and "The Song of General Kim Jong Il", presenting the august names of the peerlessly great men, "Juche", "September 9, 1948", "Songun Politics", five-pointed star, a rifle and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There appeared on the square in succession diverse columns and movements with torchlight representing the majestic appearance of Juche Korea and the unbreakable single-minded unity of the revolutionary ranks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Entering the square were ranks of torchlight marchers led by open limousines carrying young boys and girls holding high the flag of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League bearing the portrait of President Kim Il Sung and the torchlight of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The columns of youth and students passed through the square in fine array, presenting the letters "Young Vanguard" and "Devoted Defence" to represent the faith and will of the successors to the Songun revolution who would accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche, which started in Mt. Paektu, united close around the headquarters of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the participants formed letters "Glory to General!" and a floral basket in reflection of the firm determination of the hot-blooded young people to hold leader Kim Jong Il in high esteem, deeply trusting and following him, fireworks were displayed to beautifully decorate the nocturnal sky of the square on the auspicious day of September.

National Meeting Held to Mark Diamond Jubilee of DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- A national meeting was held at the Pyongyang Indoor Stadium Monday to mark the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were senior party, army and state officials, chairpersons of the friendly parties, deputies to the Supreme People's Assembly, officials of party, armed forces and power bodies, social organizations, ministries and national institutions, servicepersons of the Korean People's Army, officials in the fields of science, education, culture and arts, public health and media, bereaved families of revolutionary martyrs, labor innovators and working people in Pyongyang, the chief of the Pyongyang Mission of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front, the congratulatory group of Koreans in Japan and other congratulatory groups and delegations of Koreans and compatriots in different parts of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were representatives and staff members of foreign embassies and representatives of international organizations here and delegations of different countries, delegations and delegates of Juche idea study organizations and friendly and solidarity organizations and other foreign guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A congratulatory message presented to General Secretary Kim Jong Il on behalf of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, the Central Military Commission of the WPK and the National Defence Commission, the SPA Presidium and the Cabinet of the DPRK was conveyed by Kim Yong Nam, member of the Political Bureau of the WPK Central Committee and president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Premier of the Cabinet Kim Yong Il delivered a report at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter said that the six-decade-long history of the DPRK was a course of victory in which its army and people paved a new path for building a state centered on the popular masses under the uplifted revolutionary banner of the Juche idea, single-mindedly united around President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il, and fully demonstrated the might of a socialist power, independent in politics, self-supporting in economy and self-reliant in national defence, and a glorious path along which they strikingly showcased the validity and invincibility of the ideology, system and cause of the DPRK despite the stern tempest of the anti-imperialist struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Since the foundation of the DPRK Kim Il Sung energetically led the work to shape all lines and policies in line with the requirements and interests of its people and the specific conditions of the country and push ahead with the revolutionary struggle and construction in an independent and creative manner according to their own faith and viewpoint. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Il Sung, founder of the Songun idea and pioneer of the Songun revolution, paid primary attention to military affairs in the whole course of leading the DPRK and exerted great efforts for augmenting the military capability of the country in each period of the revolutionary development and at its each phase. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Juche-based cause of nation-building which has victoriously advanced under the banner of Songun has developed in depth to reach a new higher stage as Kim Jong Il established the Songun politics as a main socialist political mode as required by the changed environment of the times and the revolutionary development in the 1990s and embodied it in all fields. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter called for achieving the eternal prosperity of the country and the nation with the tremendous might of the servicepersons and people single-mindedly united around the headquarters of the revolution headed by Kim Jong Il, reunifying the country and wining a final victory in the revolutionary cause of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people will wage a dynamic nationwide struggle to usher in a new era of independent reunification, peace and prosperity by their concerted efforts under the uplifted banner of the historic June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration and thus surely achieve the cause of national reunification, the reporter noted, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The situation still remains tense on the Korean Peninsula due to the hostile moves of the U.S. imperialists and their satellite forces against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The army and people of the DPRK are closely watching with a high degree of revolutionary vigilance the moves of the U.S. and its followers to stifle the DPRK and will resolutely and mercilessly retaliate against any slightest provocative act of infringing upon its sovereign dignity and interests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK government will in the future, too, further develop solidarity and cooperative relations with all countries that remain friendly to it in the idea of independence, peace and friendship and make positive efforts to achieve stability and development of Asia and the rest of the world, opposing and rejecting imperialists' domination, interference and moves for a war.

Congratulatory Message to Kim Jong Il 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a congratulatory message in the joint name of the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the Workers' Party of Korea, the National Defence Commission, the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly and the Cabinet of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea on Tuesday on the occasion of the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The proclamation of the founding of the DPRK by President Kim Il Sung on Sept. 9, Juche 37 (1948), right after the country's liberation was a solemn declaration of the birth of socialist Korea, the first people's country in the former colony in the East, and marked a great event that opened up a new era of building a socialist state centered on the popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to his outstanding leadership, the army and people of the DPRK could defeat the U.S. imperialists who had boasted of being the "strongest" in the world and honorably safeguard the freedom and independence of the country and the gains of the revolution and eradicate century-old backwardness and poverty and build a socialist power, independent in politics, self-supporting in economy and self-reliant in national defence, by successfully carrying out the post-war rehabilitation and construction, socialist revolution and gigantic socialist construction on debris. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President clarified the unique theory of power building which calls for making the state power a representative of the sovereign rights of the popular masses, an organizer of the creative ability and activities, a house-holder responsible for the people's living and protector of the interests of the people for the first time in the history of the building of the socialist government and successfully embodied it, building on this land the best socialist system centered on the popular masses where they have become masters of the country and society and everything serves them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the DPRK is greeting its best day in its development, demonstrating its invincible might under the experienced and tested leadership of Kim Jong Il, the message continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to your leadership, the government of the Republic has developed to be a powerful political weapon for dynamically advancing the cause of building socialism centered on the popular masses as intended by the President, regarding the immortal Juche idea fathered by him as unshakable guidelines. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 You made sure that the Kim Il Sung Constitution was instituted and promulgated, a constitution which codified Kim Il Sung as the eternal President of the DPRK reflecting the unanimous will and desire of the army and people after the nation was seized with the profound grief over his demise. This was the most vivid manifestation of the revolutionary ethics and morality in the history of the constitution under socialism and marked a historic event that made the Republic shine forever with the august name of the President and enabled it to dynamically advance with the great revolutionary idea of the President and his undying exploits performed in the nation-building as an eternal foundation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK could steadily advance along the road of socialism of Juche despite the tempests of the complicated politics in the world where socialist power got degenerated and collapsed in various countries. This was the result of the revolutionary leadership of you who have strengthened and developed the government of the Republic as the state of its founder Kim Il Sung in name and reality with the iron faith that socialism is a science and the firm will that no change should be expected from you.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was thanks to your outstanding foresightedness and strong resolution that the Songun politics was formulated as the main political mode under socialism and the Korean-style state leadership system was established with the National Defence Commission as its core to develop the DPRK as a powerful socialist state which always emerges victorious thanks to the treasured sword of Songun.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 Never has there been such a time in the history of the Korean nation spanning 5,000 years as now when the position of the country has reached the level of a dignified power and the dignity and honor of the nation have been demonstrated to the whole world thanks to your Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 You are, indeed, a peerless patriot and a great man without parallel as you have wisely led the country to victory and glory with noblest patriotism and outstanding political caliber. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the unshakable faith and will of the army and people of the DPRK to totally entrust their destinies to you, a symbol of all victories and glory and future of Songun Korea, and achieve its eternal prosperity, single-mindedly remaining true to your idea and leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the party members, servicepersons of the People's Army and people will hold the President in high esteem as the founder of socialist Korea and eternal President of the DPRK and steadily carry forward his idea and cause and thus glorify the country as Kim Il Sung's Korea, the everlasting country of the sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will decisively foil the anti-DPRK and anti-reunification moves of the separatist forces at home and abroad, holding fast to the three charters for national reunification, and surely build an independent and prosperous reunified powerful nation on this land of three thousand ri through the concerted efforts of all Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will boost international solidarity with the world progressive people desirous of independence and wage a positive struggle to build an independent and peaceful new world.

Banquet Given by DPRK Government 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- The DPRK government arranged a banquet at the People's Palace of Culture on Sept. 9 on the occasion of the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were senior officials of the Party, the army and the state, chairpersons of friendly parties, deputies to the Supreme People's Assembly, officials of party, armed forces and power organs, public organizations, ministries, national institutions, anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters, servicepersons of the Korean People's Army, officials of scientific, educational, cultural and arts, public health and media institutions and persons of distinguished services. The chief of the Pyongyang Mission of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front, the congratulatory group of Korean residents in Japan and other overseas compatriots were among those present there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 Present there on invitation were foreign delegations, the delegations of friendly organizations and solidarity organizations of various countries on a visit to the DPRK, diplomatic envoys of different countries and representatives of international organizations here and foreign guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, made a speech at the banquet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 The speaker said that under the wise leadership of President Kim Il Sung the DPRK has turned into an invincible power demonstrating its might with independence in politics, self-support in economy and self-reliance in national defence and a genuine cradle of the Korean people, courageously weathering out stern tempest and trials of history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The President's cause of building a rich and powerful country is now being successfully carried out at a new higher stage and the DPRK has a rosy future of a great prosperous powerful nation under the leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the great fortune and the highest honor for the army and people of the DPRK to have Kim Jong Il at the helm of the Juche-based revolution, the speaker noted, and continued:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 A great prosperous powerful socialist nation of Juche is sure to emerge on this land to shed its rays all over the world and the dignity and might of the Republic will be further exalted thanks to the experienced and tested leadership of Kim Jong Il, the mental power of all the servicepersons and people single-mindedly united around the headquarters of the revolution and the invincible armed forces demonstrating their might as the strong revolutionary army of Mt. Paektu.

Homage to Kim Il Sung 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- Senior party, army and state officials, a chairperson of friendly party, leading officials of party, armed forces organs and working people's organizations visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace on September 9 to pay homage to President Kim Il Sung on the occasion of the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 They entered the hall where the statue of the President stands. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Placed before the statue of Kim Il Sung was a floral basket in the joint name of the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the Workers' Party of Korea and the National Defence Commission of the DPRK, the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly and the Cabinet of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The senior party, army and state officials paid profound tribute to the President in humble reverence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 They made deep bows to the President who built on this land socialist Korea in which the idea of believing in the people as in Heaven is embodied and laid a firm foundation for the eternal prosperity of the country and the nation.

Mass Gymnastic Display Marks Birthday of DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- The mass gymnastic display "May Country Prosper" was performed at the May Day Stadium today to celebrate the 60th birthday of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Appreciating the display were senior party, army and state officials, deputies to the Supreme People's Assembly, officials of party, armed forces and power organs, public organizations, ministries and national institutions, anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters servicepersons of the Korean People's Army, officials of scientific, educational, cultural and arts, public health and press organs, bereaved families of revolutionary martyrs, persons of merit and working people in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on invitation to enjoy the display were the chief of the Pyongyang mission of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front, the congratulatory group of Koreans in Japan and other congratulatory groups and delegations of overseas Koreans and compatriots from different regions of the world, representatives and staff members of foreign embassies and representatives of international organizations here, delegations of various countries, delegations of Juche idea study organizations and friendly and solidarity organizations and other foreign guests staying in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The mass gymnastic display made an impressive, great epic representation of the glorious history of the DPRK which shines with the revolutionary exploits of President Kim Il Sung and which has made long strides, winning victory after victory under the experienced and seasoned leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The display was highly acclaimed by the spectators as its performers made a successful ideological and artistic representation of the undying feats of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and the might of the DPRK where the army and people are making an all-out advance toward the high eminence of a great prosperous powerful nation, single-mindedly united around the headquarters of the revolution, through dynamic and graceful gymnastic movements, the presentation of diverse columns of gymnasts and formative arts and ever-changing background of the stadium.

Congratulatory Message to Kim Jong Il from Chinese Party and State Leaders 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- A congratulatory message came to Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission, Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, and Kim Yong Il, premier of the Cabinet, from Hu Jintao, general secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China and president of the People's Republic of China and chairman of the Central Military Commission of the PRC, Wu Bangguo, chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, and Wen Jiabao, premier of the State Council, on Monday on the occasion of the 60th founding anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On behalf of the Communist Party of China and the Chinese government and people, we send warm congratulations and best wishes to you and, through you, to the Workers' Party of Korea and the DPRK government and the Korean people on the occasion of the 60th founding anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The foundation of the DPRK showed that the Korean people became the master of the country and embarked on the new road of building a socialist state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the past six decades, the Korean people have achieved distinguished successes in socialist revolution and construction&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
under the leadership of President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il and the WPK in the spirit of self-reliance and fortitude. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We sincerely rejoice at them and wholeheartedly hope that the Korean people will steadily register fresh successes in seeking a way of development suited to the specific conditions of their country, promoting the overall development of economy and society and expanding exchange and cooperation with other countries, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 China and the DPRK are the friendly neighbors linked with each other by the same rivers and mountain. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The traditional Sino-DPRK friendship is steadily growing stronger thanks to the joint efforts of both sides. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will join the DPRK side in making strenuous efforts to put spurs to the development of the Sino-DPRK friendly and cooperative relations and defend the peace and security in the region in the spirit of inheriting the tradition, facing up to the future, boosting the good neighborliness, friendship and cooperation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 We wish the DPRK prosperity and the Korean people happiness.

Kim Jong Il Receives Congratulatory Letter from Russian President
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- Chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission Kim Jong Il received a congratulatory letter from Russian President Dmitri Anatoliyevich Medvedev on Monday on the occasion of the 60th founding anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Please accept my heartfelt congratulations to you on the occasion of the 60th founding anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A new sovereign state, which had a geographically and historically close relation with our country, was founded in the land of Korea on September 9, 1948. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For the past several decades since the significant day, we have gained weighty and positive experience in the mutual cooperation and implemented a lot of common plans conducive to the welfare of the peoples of the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is my belief that the traditional good-neighborly relations between our two countries will continue to grow stronger in the future, too, and thus make a distinguished contribution to ensuring peace, stability and security in the Korean Peninsula and the rest of Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 Your Excellency Kim Jong Il, &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I wish you good health and greater success in your responsible state affairs and the friendly DPRK peace and prosperity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Yours Sincerely.

Message of Greetings to Kim Jong Il from Raul Castro Ruz
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il and Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, received a message of greetings from Raul Castro Ruz, President of the Council of State and president of the Council of Ministers of Cuba, on Sept. 5 on the occasion of the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I send warmest felicitations to you on behalf of the Communist Party, government and people of Cuba on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The feelings of fraternal cooperation and solidarity that characterize the relations between Cuba and the DPRK encourage us and their most vivid manifestation is our support for the just desire of the Korean people for the complete national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I, availing myself of this opportunity, reaffirm our will to continue to boost the fraternal cooperative relations between the parties, governments and peoples of our two countries and sincerely wish you success in your work of leading the Korean nation and happiness. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Please accept my warm fraternal regards.

Anniversary of DPRK Marked
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- Leading papers today dedicate editorials to the 60th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 President Kim Il Sung's founding of the DPRK on September 9, Juche 37 (1948) marked a significant event in ushering in a new era for building a rich and powerful country for the people on this land under the banner of the Juche idea, Rodong Sinmun says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The foundation of the DPRK meant the birth of a new Korea for the people, the greatest and the most dignified one in the history of the nation spanning 5 000 years and the beginning of a glorious history of building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation in our era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has recorded great victories and miracles by bravely overcoming all kinds of tempests and trials of history with the might of the single-minded unity under the leadership of the party and the leader during the past six decades. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 The Korean people have spared no precious blood and sweat in the struggle for the sovereignty, independence and the prosperity of the country sharing their destiny with the party both during difficult days and days of glory and victory, and firmly defended the government and the socialist system of the DPRK, valuing them more precious than their own lives. The single-minded unity has grown stronger in the victorious course of history under the sacred blue and red flag of the Republic. Herein lie the key to the mightiness of the DPRK, its high dignity and honor and immensely bright future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The feats performed by the President, who bequeathed the socialist power to the Korean people and glorified the dignity and honor of the nation, working heart and soul for the prosperity of the country and the happiness of people throughout his 80 odd-year-long revolutionary career, will shine long along with the history of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The prospect of the DPRK dynamically advancing toward the bright future full of confidence is firmly guaranteed by General Secretary Kim Jong Il's scientific revolutionary idea, the politico-ideological might and the might of the single-minded unity of all servicepersons and people firmly rallied around him as one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  
 Thanks to the tremendous mental power of all servicepersons and people upholding the leader's idea and policy in single mind while devotedly safeguarding him at the cost of their lives the DPRK will continue to win victories and work miracles startling the world and exalt its might as an invincible power which no one dare provokes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson editorially stresses that the DPRK will certainly scale the eminence of a great prosperous powerful nation and shine as the country of Kim Il Sung forever as it is led by Kim Jong Il.

Floral Baskets Laid before Statues of Kim Il Sung
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- Floral baskets were laid before the statues of President Kim Il Sung on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 Servicepersons and people visited the statues of the President in different parts of the country at a time when the country is pervaded with profound reverence for Kim Il Sung, the father of socialist Korea, founder and leader of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seen standing before the statue of the President on Mansu Hill was a floral basket from Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea, chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission and supreme commander of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Floral tribute was paid to the statue of the President in the name of party, armed forces and power organs, public organizations, ministries, national institutions, KPA units and scientific, educational, cultural, arts, public health and media institutions and factories, enterprises, schools, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A floral basket in the name of the Pyongyang Mission of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front was placed before the statue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 The visitors made bows in reverence before the statue of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 Floral baskets were laid before the statues of the President standing at different units including Kim Il Sung University, Kim Il Sung Military University, the Ministry of People's Security and the Pyongyang Schoolchildren's Palace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Servicepersons, people and school youth and children across the country visited the statues of the President in their residential areas and paid floral tribute to him.

Wreaths and Floral Baskets Laid before Cemeteries and Monument to Victory in War
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- Wreaths were laid before the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery on Mt. Taesong and the Patriotic Martyrs Cemetery and floral baskets before the Monument to Victory in the Fatherland Liberation War on Monday on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seen on the wreath-laying stands of the cemeteries were wreaths sent by Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea, chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission and supreme commander of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the wreath- and floral basket-laying ceremonies were senior party, army and state officials, a chairman of a friendly party, officials of the party, armed forces and power organs, public organizations, ministries and national institutions, servicepersons of the Korean People's Army and working people in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wreaths in the name of the Central Committee of the WPK and the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly and the Cabinet of the DPRK were laid on the wreath-laying stands of the cemeteries and a floral basket in the joint name of the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the WPK before the main theme sculpture "Victory" of the above-said monument. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Floral tribute was paid at the cemeteries and the monument in the name of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces, working people's organizations, ministries, national institutions, KPA units and scientific, educational, culture and art, public health and media institutions and party and power organs and factories, farms and universities in Pyongyang.

Reception Given for Overseas Compatriots
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- A reception was given by General Secretary Kim Jong Il for overseas compatriots on Tuesday on the occasion of the 60th founding of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on invitation were congratulatory groups, delegations and visiting groups of overseas compatriots and other overseas Koreans staying in the socialist homeland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Kim Yu Ho, director of the Bureau of Service for Overseas Compatriots, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 Speeches were made at the reception.

Reception Given for Adherents to Juche Idea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- The DPRK government gave a reception at Pyongyang Koryo Hotel Monday in honor of delegations and delegates of Juche idea study organizations on the occasion of the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Director-General of the International Institute of the Juche Idea Vishwanath, a delegation of the Secretariat of the IIJI headed by Secretary General Kenichi Ogami and delegations and delegates of Juche idea study organizations from different countries and regions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, Choe Sang Sun, chairman of the Korean Social Scientists Society, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Yang Hyong Sop in a speech made at the reception said that President Kim Il Sung founded the DPRK and turned it into a socialist power, independent in politics, self-supporting in the economy and self-reliant in national defence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He noted that the President's immortal idea of nation-building and his feats and the invincible history of the DPRK are shining more brilliantly thanks to General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed thanks to the adherents to the Juche idea for having contributed to accomplishing the cause of global independence through their positive activities to study and disseminate the Juche idea and extended invariable support and solidarity to the Korean people in their just cause of socialist construction and national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Vishwanath, speaking next, said that Kim Il Sung, the great sun, is immortal for the undying feats performed for the Korean revolution and socialist construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He noted: The Korean people are firmly preserving the feats of the President and effecting new changes in socialist construction day by day. These would be unthinkable without the energetic leadership of Kim Jong Il.

