Congratulatory Message to Kim Jong Il from Chongryon
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a congratulatory message from the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) on Sept. 9 on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message said that all officials of Chongryon and compatriots in Japan greeting the 60th founding anniversary of the DPRK are full of high national pride and joy of flying blue and red flags of the Republic in every nook and corner of Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that they feel very grateful for the profound loving care of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il who always have led them along the road of patriotism over the past six decades, the message stressed that the love and care with which the President personally led Chongryon and the compatriots in Japan in their every step and helped them set an example in the world overseas residents movement are recorded as legends in the history of the movement of the Koreans in Japan. It added that the President is an eternal father of the compatriots in Japan and his care is the embrace of the exceptionally benevolent homeland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 Pointing out that Kim Jong Il who has successfully carried forward and developed President's cause of nation-building has clearly indicated the road for the work of Chongryon and compatriots in Japan to follow and wisely led them, deeply considerate of it and the safety of the compatriots in Japan at all times, while making the forced march accompanied by endless journeys for on-the-spot guidance to the building of a great prosperous powerful nation and in those days of commanding the confrontation with the U.S. to victory in the historic period of more than a decade during which he ushered in a great heyday for the Republic with his Songun politics, the message emphasized that Chongryon officials and compatriots in Japan could firmly preserve the precious patriotic tradition of sharing their destiny with the socialist homeland full of confidence and optimism despite the Japanese reactionaries' brutal suppression because Kim Jong Il trusted them as true loyalists and ardent patriots who share weal and woe with the homeland and encouraged them in consolidating the single-minded unity of the Chongryon ranks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
