 At the end of the ceremony there was a forum for smashing the suppression of the federation, getting the NSL abrogated and checking the suppression of candlelight actions.

Japan's Undisguised Moves to Grab Tok Islet Denounced in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- The Solidarity for New Society, the National Solidarity for Protecting Tok Islet and other organizations in south Korea denounced Japan's moves to grab Tok Islet through statements and press conferences on Sep. 5. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organizations expressed indignation at the Japanese government which held a cabinet meeting that day and adopted a 2008 defense white paper in which it claimed Tok Islet belongs to Japan's territory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It charged that this reckless action taken by Japan in less than two months since it mentioned "dominium on Tok Islet" in the "guidelines for teaching in the new academic year" and it was a dangerous action bringing into bolder relief its wild ambition to grab Tok Islet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organizations urged the Lee Myung Bak "government" to take strong and substantial countermeasures against the Japanese authorities' moves to seize Tok Islet.

Kim Jong Il's Work Published in Czech Republic
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il's famous work "Let Us Hold the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung in High Esteem as Eternal President of Our Republic" was brought out in pamphlet by the Futra Publishing House of the Czech Republic. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work, published on July 11 and 19, Juche 83 (1994), calls upon the Korean people to always hold President Kim Il Sung in high esteem as they  did when he was alive and indicates the tasks for defending his idea and undying feats and creditably carrying forward and developing them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A ceremony of releasing the work took place at the above-said house on September 2. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The general director of the house said at the ceremony that the work reflects the steadfast will of Kim Jong Il to perfectly carry forward and develop the cause of the President who founded the DPRK.  We are convinced that the Korean people will certainly build a great prosperous powerful nation in Korea by carrying through the behests of the President, he added.

DPRK's Birthday Marked in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 8 (KCNA) -- Meetings, photo exhibitions and film shows were held in India, Pakistan and Laos between August 28 and September 1 on the occasion of the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed in the photo exhibition halls were photos showing the undying feats of President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il and photos introducing the glorious history and achievements of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the meetings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 J. K. Patel, director of the Indian Institute for Foreign Policy Studies, said that the DPRK could fully demonstrate the advantages and invincibility of Korean-style socialism in the grim tempest of the anti-imperialist struggle, making heroic epic of creation and construction over the past six decades as the President pioneered the revolutionary cause of Juche and provided the eternal foundation for its accomplishment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The minister of Public Welfare of the Sind Provincial Government of Pakistan said that the Korean people realized the socialist industrialization on the debris in a short period of 14 years after the war and the DPRK turned into a socialist power independent in politics, self-supporting in the economy and self-reliant in national defence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The vice-director general of the Laos-Korea Tin Company noted that watching the film dealing with the revolutionary exploits of the President, he came to know better about Kim Il Sung's immortal exploits for nation-building and the DPRK, which has been strengthened and developed thanks to the Songun politics of Kim Jong Il. The DPRK will further prosper with each passing day under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il, he said.
 A message of greetings to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting in Pakistan.

DPRK's Socialist Cause Supported in South Africa
